msgid "General Properties"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_properties.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:25-1
msgid ""
"The General page of the Frame Properties dialog contains basic settings. Many "
"of these settings contain the information entered when a frame is created. Use "
"this page to modify those settings you feel you need to change after you have "
"created your frame."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_properties.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:26-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Frame Name</b>: Lists the name you assigned "
"when you created your frame."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_properties.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:27-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Synopsis and Description</b>: Lists "
"information that is used in Keyboard Help, <b>INSERT+1</b>, when you press the "
"keystroke assigned to your frame."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_properties.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:28-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Prompts - Spoken, Brailled, Tutor</b>: Lists "
"information for frames used to provide prompt information for controls."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_properties.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:29-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Keystroke</b>: Lists the keystroke which "
"activates the On Frame Key event for the frame, causing any assigned actions "
"to take place. If you copy a frame from another version of JAWS, or from "
"another computer running JAWS, you need to reassign this keystroke."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_properties.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:30-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Priority</b>: Sets the relative priority of "
"frames. This is useful when you have multiple frames within the same area of "
"an application as it allows you to determine which one takes precedence over "
"the others. The lower the value, the higher the priority."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_properties.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:31-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\frame_properties.htm+html.body.h2:31-1"
msgid "Validation Rules Properties"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_properties.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:32-1
msgid ""
"The Validation Rules page of the Frame Properties dialog contains a list of "
"the rules used to determine when the frame is active. The rules compare "
"information from your application with information specified when the frame "
"was created. The order in which rules are listed is the order in which they "
"are processed."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_properties.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:33-1
msgid ""
"The list specifies if the rule is on or off, the type of rule, the comparison "
"type, and the value being compared."
msgstr ""

